1 C. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
2 (ODAFF), in collaboration with the Oklahoma Conservation Commission
3 (OCC), Oklahoma Water Resources Board (OWRB) shall establish and
4 oversee the Salt Cedar Eradication Program which shall include:
5 1. Conducting surveys to identify and map salt cedar
6 infestations in Oklahoma counties within the Upper Red River Basin;
7 2. Developing and implementing science-based eradication
8 strategies, including mechanical removal, chemical treatments, and
9 biological controls;
10 3. Provide technical and financial assistance to eligible
11 landowners; and
12 4. Monitor and evaluate the effectiveness of eradication
13 efforts.
14 D. Landowners in identified high-priority areas may be required
15 to participate in eradication programs or face penalties for
16 noncompliance.
17 E. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry,
18 shall establish guidelines for participation, including cost-sharing
19 arrangements and reimbursement opportunities.
20 F. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
21 is authorized to promulgate any rules and procedures to effectuate
22 the provisions of this act, which shall include setting penalties
23 for landowners for noncompliance.
24
