1 G. The Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
2 shall submit an annual report to the Governor, Speaker of the
3 Oklahoma House of Representatives, to the President Pro Tempore of
4 the Oklahoma State Senate, and to the chairs of the appropriation
5 chairs of the Oklahoma House of Representatives and the Oklahoma
6 State Senate outlining the following:
7 1. Progress of eradication efforts;
8 2. Expenditures and funding needs; and
9 3. Recommendations for continued salt cedar management.
10 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
11 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 3-8-203 of Title 27A, unless
12 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
13 There is hereby created in the State Treasury a revolving fund
14 for the Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry
15 (ODAFF) to be designated the "Salt Cedar Eradication Revolving
16 Fund". The fund shall be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal
17 year limitations, and shall consist of all monies received by the
18 Oklahoma Department of Agriculture, Food, and Forestry from
19 appropriations, federal grants or funds, municipal contributions,
20 private contributions, and any other sources, including interest
21 earned from the income in the fund, that are designated for deposit
22 to such fund or designated for duties associated with removal and
23 eradication of salt cedars in Beckham and Jackson counties. All
24 monies accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby appropriated
